<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 4:30PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Richland
County through 530 PM MDT...
At 429 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Brockton, or 16 miles southeast of Poplar, moving east
at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northern Richland
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
northeastern Montana.</instruction>
